<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="optional-adj">optional <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ɒpʃənl/    美 /'ɑːpʃənl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>可选择的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Taking <strong>optional subjects</strong> will enrich our mind.
上选修课可以充实我们的头脑。</p><footer>2015 湖南</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The service would be optional for cell phone users.
手机用户可以自由选择这项服务。</p><footer>2008 山东改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>According to Professor Johnson, we don't have to read the book if we don't want to, as it is<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ （可选择的）.  （2020天津）  </li>
<li>In that school, English is compulsory for all students, but French and Russian are <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (option).  （2011 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. optional  2. optional  </p></div>